            <p class="text-gray-400 mt-2 text-lg">Upload your data to analyze your followers, following & mutuals.</p>
        </header>

        <!-- Instructions Section -->
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-700 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">‚öôÔ∏è How to Get Your Instagram Data</h2>
            <div class="text-gray-300 space-y-3">
                <p>You need to request a copy of your information from Instagram. This is a manual process that can only be done through the app or website.</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
                    <li>‚û°Ô∏è Go to your Instagram profile, then navigate to <strong class="font-semibold">Settings ‚Üí Accounts Center ‚Üí Your Information and Permissions</strong>.</li>
                    <li>‚û°Ô∏è Click <strong class="font-semibold">Download Your Information</strong> and then <a href="https://www.instagram.com/download/request" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline font-semibold">Request a download</a>.</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ Select your profile and choose <strong class="font-semibold">Select types of information</strong>.</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ From the options, select only <strong class="font-semibold">Followers and following</strong>.</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ Set the format to <strong class="font-semibold">JSON</strong> and the date range to <strong class="font-semibold">All time</strong>.</li>
                    <li>üöÄ Finalize the request. Instagram will email you a link to download your data. Unzip the file to find your `followers_1.json` and `following.json` files.</li>
